{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"@"},{"kind":"attribute","preciseIdentifier":"s:ScM","text":"MainActor"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSButton"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"Hierarchies","type":"heading","text":"Hierarchies","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Five hierarchies are proposed for all layouts:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"default (by default)","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": Default buttons are used for actions which are not mandatory or essential for the user.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"strong","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":": Should be singular and prominent, limited to one per view."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It should be reserved for the most critical action, such as “Next,” “Save,” “Submit,” etc. It is a “call for action”."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"brand"}]},{"type":"text","text":": A brand primary color alternative to the "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"strong","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" button."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To be used sparingly for high-value specific actions or to visually anchor a brand moment. Do not use it as the default primary button in your interfaces."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A button with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSButton.Hierarchy.Brand"},{"type":"text","text":" hierarchy is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"minimal"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Minimal buttons are commonly used for actions that are considered less crucial. They can be used independently or together with a strong button."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"negative"}]},{"type":"text","text":": Negative buttons should be used sparingly to warn of a destructive action,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for example, delete or remove, typically resulting in the opening of a confirmation dialog."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A button with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSButton.Hierarchy.Negative"},{"type":"text","text":" hierarchy is not allowed as a direct or indirect child of an "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]}]},{"anchor":"Code-samples","type":"heading","text":"Code samples","level":2},{"code":["    \/\/ Icon only with default hierarchy","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), hierarchy: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\")) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text only with negative hierarchy","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", hierarchy: .negative,  style: .default) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","    \/\/ Or simpler","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", hierarchy: .negative) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ A loading button","    OUDSButton(text: \"Delete\", style: .loading) { \/* the action to process *\/ }","","    \/\/ Text and icon with strong hierarchy","    OUDSButton(icon: Image(\"ic_heart\"), text: \"Validate\", hierarchy: .strong) { \/* the action to process *\/ }"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Styles","type":"heading","text":"Styles","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Two style are available:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"default (by default)","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":": used in the normal usage of button. The aspect of the button changes for  states ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"disabled"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"pressed","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"hovered","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" or normal (i.e. ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"enabled","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":")","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"loading"}]},{"type":"text","text":": used after button was clicked and probably data are requested before navigate to a next screen or get updated data."}]}]}]},{"anchor":"Rounded-layout","type":"heading","text":"Rounded layout","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Buttons can have rounded layouts to be favored in more emotional, immersive contexts or those tied to specific visual identities."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For standard or business-oriented journeys, keep the default corners."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This evolution addresses the need for flexibility in adapting the design to some brand contexts."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To activate the rounded button behavior, set to true the  "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"oudsRoundedButton"},{"type":"text","text":" environment variable"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"at the root level of the view hierarchy (i.e. can be applied on the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSThemeableView"},{"type":"text","text":"),"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to be sure all buttons in the application are rounded."}]},{"code":["    \/\/ Add themeable view to your app root view to use the OrangeTheme","    OUDSThemeableView(theme: OrangeTheme()) {","        YourRootView() \/\/ With some views with Buttons","    }","    .environment(\\.oudsRoundedButton, true)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Colored-surface","type":"heading","text":"Colored surface","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If button is placed on colored surface using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OUDSColoredSurface"},{"type":"text","text":", the default colors (content, background and border) are automatically adjusted to switch to monochrome mode."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Remark: Today it is not allowed to place a Negative nor a Brand button on a colored surface."}]}]},{"anchor":"Specific-behavior","type":"heading","text":"Specific behavior","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For accessibility reasons, if the system settings for reducing motion is enabled, the loading indicator does not move."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For ecodesign reasons, if the device is in low power mode, the loading indicator does not move."}]},{"anchor":"Design-documentation","type":"heading","text":"Design documentation","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/unified-design-system.orange.com\/472794e18\/p\/48a788-button"}]},{"anchor":"Themes-rendering","type":"heading","text":"Themes rendering","level":2},{"anchor":"Orange","type":"heading","text":"Orange","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"component_button_enabled_strong_Orange","type":"image"}]},{"anchor":"Orange-Business-Tools","type":"heading","text":"Orange Business Tools","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inline